A native doctor and two other suspects have been arrested by the operatives of the Enugu State Police Command for alleged kidnapping. The native doctor, Aneke-Ikenga and the other two suspects were alleged to have kidnapped one Amaechi Oguama (male) on October 20, 2021, collected a sum of N10 million ransom from the victim’s family and never released him till date. The state Police Public Relations Officer, Daniel Ndukwe, said they were among 45 suspected criminals arrested in Enugu between March and April 2022. -Advertisement- According to him, the names of the suspects are Oko Chukwudi popularly known as ‘Anka-Dede’; Ifeanyi Eze a.k.a. “Abrinanwa” and Sunday Ede Aneke, a native doctor who is popularly known as ‘Aneke-Ikenga’. The PPRO said that the suspects were arrested on March 22 and 24, 2022 by operatives serving in the CP Monitoring Unit. He said that the suspects, who hail from Akpugo in Nkanu West local government area, were members of a criminal gang that specialised in the kidnapping. He said that three members of the gang, whom he gave their names one Chioma Uwa (f) a.k.a. “Dr Happiness”; Chekwube Nwatu (m) a.k.a. “Cheche” and Emeka Uwa (m) a.k.a. “Akimbo” and had earlier been arrested, arraigned in court and remanded in the Enugu Correctional Maximum Custodial Centre “The newly arrested suspects confessed to having been actively involved in the kidnapping of the said victim and the receipt of the ransom of over ten million Naira (N10,000,000.00) by the criminal gang. One Berretta pistol with 1 .9mm round of live ammunition was recovered from them.” POLL “Meanwhile, the suspects will be further arraigned in court and prosecuted alongside the previous suspects, once the supplementary investigation into the case is concluded.,” he said He advised citizens of the state to remain law-abiding, and vigilant and continue to support the police by promptly reporting criminals and their activities to the nearest Police Station